3. Create an OSL node and paste the shader code into the Code field.
4. Connect the 'Out Color' output of the OSL node to the appropriate input on the Redshift material node (diffuse color, etc.).

After applying the material with the corrected OSL shader to your sphere, the checkerboard pattern should now take into consideration the UV mapping, resulting in a more uniform application of the pattern across the geometry.
